<FIRST>r a AM-DrugShooting     10-23 0250</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Drug Shooting,0255</SECOND>
<HEAD>DEA Agent Shoots and Kills Suspect in Midtown New York</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY39, 40</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOSEPH NEFF</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A suspect in a drug investigation was shot to
death in Rockefeller Center by federal agents Monday after a drug
buy went sour and the man drove off, dragging an agent down the
street, authorities said.
   The Drug Enforcement Administration agent, who rolled off the
car before it crashed into the back of a bus, suffered minor
injuries, officials said. No one else was hurt.
   The violence occurred around 7 p.m. on 50th Street in
Rockefeller Center, an area popular with tourists. More than 100
people watched as the suspect was handcuffed, then treated for a
chest wound on the ground next to the car.
   The suspect was dead when taken to Bellevue Hospital, said
hospital administrator Peter Schectman. The man was not immediately
identified.
   According to DEA spokeswoman Mary Cooper, another undercover
agent had arranged to buy 4 pounds of pure cocaine from the
suspect. Once the agent saw the cocaine, a signal was given and
other officers approached the car to arrest the man, Cooper said.
   As they identified themselves, the suspect drove off, she said.
An agent got caught in the car and was dragged along for about 100
feet.
   The agent fired two shots and rolled off the car into the street
as another agent fired at least one shot, Cooper said.
   The suspect was not armed, officials said.
</TEXT>
