<FIRST>d a PM-SFQuake-TravelPoll     10-23 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-SF Quake-Travel Poll,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prequake Poll Names San Francisco as Best American City</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   San Francisco was named the best of the American
cities to visit, but the honor comes at the worst of times.
   The city by the bay, still trying to recover from Tuesday's
devastating earthquake, was named the favorite American city Sunday
the Conde Nast Traveler's Readers' Choice Poll.
   The results from the second annual poll, which appear in the
November issue of the Conde Nast Traveler, were announced at the
opening of the American Society of Travel Agents World Congress in
Miami.
   The poll was conducted prior to the earthquake, which measured
6.9 on the Richter scale and killed at least 59 in northern
California.
   Asked their favorite U.S. city to visit, readers answered San
Francisco, followed by Boston and Seattle. San Francisco was ranked
fourth among cities world-wide, after Florence, Paris and Vienna,
Austria.
