<HEAD>Police Officer Killed by Man Who Also Dies in Gun Battle, Police
said</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to CORRECT that police commissioner didn't
say officer shot gunman, clarify that it isn't clear who did; pick up 5th
graf, `Two officers ...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A police officer was shot and killed today
during a shootout with a gunman who also was shot to death, the
police commissioner said.
   Patrolman Albert Valentino, a 12-year department veteran, died
after being shot once just below and to one side of his bulletproof
vest, said Commissioner Willie Williams. Valentino and two other
officers had been investigating a report of a break-in.
   ``When the officer approached, the man pulled a gun and fired
and the officer also fired and both were killed,'' said Sgt. Johnny
Johnson, a homicide detective. Johnson said there was no indication
of any break-in.
   Killed with Valentino, 37, was George Poindexter, 21, police
spokesman Ed Tenuto said. It was not immediately clear who fired
the shots that killed Poindexter.
   Two officers who also responded to the call were not injured,
police said.
   A 28-year-old bystander coming out of a bar was grazed in the
foot during the exchange of gunfire, police said. He was treated at
a hospital and released.
   Valentino was the first Philadelphia officer shot and killed in
the line of duty since two officers died in 1986, Williams said.
   Last month, Williams ordered all city police officers to wear
bulletproof vests because of a national rise in street violence.
</TEXT>
