<TEXT>
   Rep. Jack Brooks, chairman of the House
Judiciary Committee, underwent hospital tests Monday after
suffering abdominal pains during a flight from Texas to Washington,
his office announced.
   Brooks, a Texas Democrat, was being treated at Bethesda Naval
Hospital to determine the cause of the pain, his office said in a
brief statement. He entered the hospital on Sunday.
   ``According to Brooks' office, he will be hospitalized for
several days for observation and evaluation of the tests,'' the
statement said.
   Dean of the Texas congressional delegation, the 66-year-old
cigar chomping ex-Marine was first elected to the House in 1952. He
took over as chairman of the Judiciary Committee this year, after
serving as chairman of the House Government Operations Committee.

