<HEAD>Former President Home From Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Habib Bourguiba, ousted
from power in 1987, has returned home from three weeks in the
hospital, the Ministry of Health said Monday.
   Bourguiba, 86, was in satisfactory condition following prostate
surgery he underwent July 29, the ministry said.
   He entered Charles Nicolle Hospital on Sept. 29. He returned
Sunday to Monastir, the city on Tunisia's southern coast where he
was born, the ministry said.
   After ruling the country since 1957, Bourguiba was ousted from
power Nov. 7, 1987 by his prime minister, Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali,
who said the aging president had become senile and physically unfit
to hold office.
