<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Libya-Flights     10-23 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Libya-Flights,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Libya to Suspend Flights to Remember the Deported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Libya will suspend all domestic and international
flights for 12 hours later this week to commemorate deportations
under Italian colonial rule, Libya's official news agency said
Monday.
   All flights, as well as international communications, will be
suspended from 6 a.m. to 6 p.m. Thursday, the JANA news agency said
in a dispatch monitored in Rome.
   Libya has taken the same action in recent years on Oct. 26 to
mark what it calls a ``day of mourning'' for Libyans deported to
Italy during colonial rule from 1911 to the end of World War II.
   Libya says at least 4,000 Libyans were deported.
