<HEAD>Astronauts Couldn't Study Quake Area from Shuttle</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-SF Quake, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EDWARDS AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The crew of Atlantis was
informed of the Bay Quake but was unable to make any observations
from orbit, a NASA official said after the space shuttle landed
Monday.
   ``They took no photographs of the area because their ground
track didn't go that far north,'' said William B. Lenoir, acting
associate administrator for space flight. The ground track is the
path formed by points that the shuttle is flying over.
   The crew spent time filming the Earth during the five-day
mission but it wasn't known if anything related to the quake would
have been visible.
