<HEAD>President Signs Increase In Head Start Funds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush signed a law Monday to increase
spending for the Head Start program for poor, pre-school children
by $147 million for the current fiscal year.
   The move increases Head Start funds to $1.6 billion.
