<HEAD>Newborn Kidnapped From Washington Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 18-day-old infant awaiting adoption was
abducted from D.C. General Hospital Monday by a woman who posed as
a volunteer to the obstetrics ward, officials said.
   The kidnapping happened around lunchtime.
   ``At that hour of the day, mothers are coming in to feed their
babies ... babies who are at the hospital,'' said hospital
spokeswoman Ann Chisholm. ``There is a lot of activity at that time
(and) this person supposedly posed as a volunteer.''
   The black male infant weighs six pounds, 10 ounces and is 19
inches long, hospital officials said. He was wrapped in a yellow
blanket and was wearing a newborn identification bracelet dated
Oct. 6.
   The woman authorities believe abducted the baby was described as
a black woman in her 20s, weighing between 230 pounds and 250
pounds with shoulder-length cornrows.
   ``We have no idea at this point'' who the woman is that took the
infant, Ms. Chisolm said.
