<HEAD>London Shares Higher At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rose in light trading Monday on
cautious hopes for British trade figures for September, to be
announced Tuesday.
   ``There is a growing feeling that it's about time we had a good
trade number,'' said one London dealer. ``If so, it would give the
market an excuse to rally.''
   Analysts were expecting a current account deficit of 1.6 billion
pounds, or $2.5 billion, for September, compared with August's 2
billion-pound shortfall.
   With many players waiting for the trade figures, most early
dealings Monday were limited to market makers, who were ``shuffling
positions,'' one trader said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was at a
session high of 2,194.6 points, up 15.5 points, or 0.7 percent. At
its lowest, the index stood at 2,179.5.
   Volume was a very light 127.1 million shares, compared with
206.9 million shares at the same time Friday.
