several days of sluggish growth in the economy, perhaps setting the
stage for lower rates.
   But many observers on the Street have also voiced increasing
concern lately over what that prospect means for corporate profits.
   In addition, brokers said, investors seemed inclined to take a
cautious approach to stocks until the market settles down a bit
after its dramatic swings in the past couple of weeks.
   UAL climbed 8\ to 176} on word that a labor-management group,
which earlier couldn't get the financing it wanted for a planned
buyout of the company, was working on a revised offer.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
gained .30 to 192.42. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index was up .05 at 382.62.
