<FIRST>r f BC-RamadaExtension     10-23 0108</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Ramada Extension,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ramada Announces Extension in Sale of Hotel Business</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ramada Inc. announced Monday that it and New York
Hotel Holdings Ltd. have agreed to extend until Feb. 28 the sale of
Ramada's hotel business to the Hong Kong company.
   The $540 million sale is part of Ramada's planned restructuring,
which the company it had postponed because of unfavorable
conditions in the junk-bond market.
   Along with selling its hotel business, Ramada plans to form a
new company, Aztar Corp. to operate its Nevada and New Jersey
casinos.
   Ramada said Monday its board Friday approved the extension
beyond the original Nov. 30 expiration date.
</TEXT>
